dismissalText.commentary: Alick Athanaze b Hazlewood 13 (31b 0x4 0x6 41m) SR: 41.93

dismissalComment.html: A horrible misjudgement from Athanaze gives Hazlewood his 250th Test wicket! The nipbacker has been having Athanaze in some trouble for a while now - a few misses and a couple of inside edges. And it is the one that comes back in from a length outside off that ends his stay in the middle in his first Test in Australia. Looks to leave the ball on a length but ended up misjudging it and the ball moves back in to hit the off pole

dismissalComment.html: Excellent catch from Hodge at deep square leg! dismissalComment.html: Huge appeal for lbw, the umpire shakes his head. Did it pitch in line? "I think it pitched in line," Labuschagne is heard saying on the stump mic and Australia opt for the review. Greaves went back to the length ball and missed the flick and was hit on the knee-roll of the front pad. The only question is whether the ball pitched in line, because Lyon is bowling from around the stumps. It did and Australia have a wicket at the stroke of stumps. They are still hanging around, with perhaps the umpires asking Cummins if Australia want the half hour. They decide against it and walk back to the dressing room
